x root: `.codex-team/`\n    48\t\n    49\t- `team-space.json`: workspace metadata with `team_id`, `workspace`, `created_at`, `protocol_version`, and `mode`.\n    50\t- `team.md`: human-readable operating brief. It may hold shared goals, rules, and links, but it is not the structured task source of truth.\n    51\t- `tasks/<task_id>.json`: one JSON object per task. Minimal fields are `task_id`, `title`, `owner`, `status`, `priority`, `dependencies`, `inputs`, `goal`, `acceptance_criteria`, `artifacts`, `lease_until`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, and optional `result`.\n    52\t- `events/events.jsonl`: append-only event stream. Each line is one JSON object with `event_id`, `type`, `timestamp`, and event-specific fields such as `task_id`, `agent_id`, `workspace`, or `payload`.\n    53\t- `inbox/<agent_id>.jsonl`: append-only per-agent messages. Each line is one JSON object with `message_id`, `target_agent_id`, `created_at`, `type`, and message-specific fields such as `task_id`, `agent_id`, or `payload`.\n    54\t- `agents/<agent_id>.json`: latest known agent state with `agent_id`, `state`, `current_task_id`, `heartbeat_at`, `last_error`, and `updated_at`.\n    55\t- `views/`: reserved for generated read models. It must not become the source of truth for task, event, inbox, or agent state.\n    56\t\n    57\tIDs should remain filename-safe. Structured writes should prefer `tasks/`, `events/`, `inbox/`, and `agents/` over parsing free text from `team.md`.\n    58\t\n    17\t## Current Slice\n    18\t\n    19\t- [ ] Execution slice — document the completion result envelope shape for Task 3 supervisor/worker flow.\n    20\t\n    21\t## Next Handoff\n    22\t\n    23\t- Loop type just completed: analysis; event-tail recovery was verified and Task 2 restart-recovery hardening was closed.\n    24\t- Keep the mailbox cadence at 1 minute unless the user explicitly overrides it.\n    25\t- Current milestone: follow-on track — `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md`.\n    26\t- Next slice: add a minimal result-envelope schema note under Task 3 in `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md`, matching the current `completeTaskForThread` payload shape without changing runtime behavior.\n    27\t- Keep the next pass non-destructive: do not change mailbox UI, stale-lease recovery, broader supervisor flow, packaging rules, or board/tab semantics.\n    28\t- Keep the next pass bounded to documentation/schema alignment before marking any Task 3 checkbox complete.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
